<section class="section" style="background-color: #F0F0F0;">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 3rem; font-size: 3rem;">
      Timeline of a Revolution
    </h2>
    
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div style="border-left: 4px solid #000; padding-left: 3rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        <div style="background: #fff; padding: 1.5rem; border: 2px solid #000; position: relative; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <div style="position: absolute; left: -3.5rem; top: 1.5rem; width: 20px; height: 20px; background: #FF0000; border: 4px solid #000; transform: rotate(45deg);"></div>
          <h3 style="color: #FF0000; font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">1920s - 1960s</h3>
          <h4 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Swiss Style Dominates</h4>
          <p>The International Typographic Style emerges in Switzerland. It emphasizes grid-based layouts, sans-serif typography (Helvetica), and "less is more." It becomes synonymous with corporate design.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background: #fff; padding: 1.5rem; border: 2px solid #000; position: relative; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <div style="position: absolute; left: -3.5rem; top: 1.5rem; width: 20px; height: 20px; background: #0000FF; border: 4px solid #000; transform: rotate(45deg);"></div>
          <h3 style="color: #0000FF; font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">1963</h3>
          <h4 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Weingart Arrives at Basel</h4>
          <p>Wolfgang Weingart moves to Basel, Switzerland and enrolls in the Basel School of Design—the birthplace of classical Swiss Typography.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background: #fff; padding: 1.5rem; border: 2px solid #000; position: relative; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <div style="position: absolute; left: -3.5rem; top: 1.5rem; width: 20px; height: 20px; background: #FFFF00; border: 4px solid #000; transform: rotate(45deg);"></div>
          <h3 style="color: #FF0000; font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">1968</h3>
          <h4 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">The Teaching Begins</h4>
          <p>Weingart begins teaching typography at Basel. He believes Swiss Typography has become "stagnant, sterile, and anonymous" and sets out to breathe new life into it.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background: #fff; padding: 1.5rem; border: 2px solid #000; position: relative; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <div style="position: absolute; left: -3.5rem; top: 1.5rem; width: 20px; height: 20px; background: #FF0000; border: 4px solid #000; transform: rotate(45deg);"></div>
          <h3 style="color: #0000FF; font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Early 1970s</h3>
          <h4 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Swiss Punk Emerges</h4>
          <p>Weingart develops experimental techniques: diagonal type, mixed typefaces, intentionally broken grids. The movement is officially born.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background: #fff; padding: 1.5rem; border: 2px solid #000; position: relative;">
          <div style="position: absolute; left: -3.5rem; top: 1.5rem; width: 20px; height: 20px; background: #0000FF; border: 4px solid #000; transform: rotate(45deg);"></div>
          <h3 style="color: #FFFF00; background: #000; display: inline-block; padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem; font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Today</h3>
          <h4 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Legacy Lives On</h4>
          <p>Swiss Punk's influence appears in music posters, experimental web design, and anywhere designers reject rigid corporate aesthetics.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

